---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import MagneticButton from '../../components/MagneticButton.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="Afri Educare Alliance" description="Case study: Embedding ethics into storytelling from day one.">

  <section class="pt-32 pb-12 bg-warm-white">
    <div class="max-w-[800px] mx-auto px-6 md:px-16">
      <a href="/projects" class="text-[13px] text-text-soft no-underline hover:text-terracotta transition-colors mb-6 inline-block reveal">&larr; Back to Projects</a>
      <h1 class="font-serif text-[38px] lg:text-[48px] text-navy leading-[1.1] reveal">Afri Educare Alliance</h1>
      <p class="font-serif text-[20px] text-text-muted mt-3 reveal">Embedding ethics into storytelling from day one.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="py-6 bg-warm-white">
    <div class="max-w-[800px] mx-auto px-6 md:px-16">
      <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-6 text-[13px] text-text-soft border-y border-navy/[0.06] py-5 reveal">
        <div><span class="text-navy font-medium">Client:</span> Afri Educare Alliance</div>
        <div><span class="text-navy font-medium">Role:</span> Co-Founder, Board Member & Communications Lead</div>
        <div><span class="text-navy font-medium">Timeline:</span> Ongoing since 2016</div>
      </div>
      <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2 mt-4 reveal">
        <span class="text-[11px] px-3 py-1 rounded-full cat-ethical">Advocacy & Ethical Storytelling</span>
        <span class="text-[11px] px-3 py-1 rounded-full cat-community">Communication & PR Education</span>
        <span class="text-[11px] px-3 py-1 rounded-full cat-lifestyle">Personal Branding & Voice</span>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="py-16 bg-warm-white">
    <div class="max-w-[800px] mx-auto px-6 md:px-16 space-y-12">

      <div class="bg-cream rounded-lg p-6 border-l-3 border-amber reveal">
        <p class="text-[14px] text-navy leading-relaxed">
          <strong>A Note on This Partnership:</strong> My work with AECA originates from my foundational role as its Co-Founder. At Tama PR, we offer the same depth of strategic communications counsel and ethical storytelling services to our external clients&mdash;mission-driven brands and organizations seeking to align their narrative with their impact.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="reveal">
        <h2 class="font-serif text-[24px] text-navy mb-4">Philosophy & Alignment</h2>
        <div class="space-y-4 text-[16px] leading-[1.8] text-text-muted">
          <p>
            Afri Educare Alliance was founded on a belief that its work should one day no longer be necessary&mdash;that a more humane, equitable society would ensure every child has access to education, healthcare, and basic dignity without intervention.
          </p>
          <p>
            Tama PR&rsquo;s collaboration with AECA is grounded in this philosophy. The communications work is not only about visibility or advocacy, but about reinforcing a long-term vision where systems serve people by default, and community support becomes a shared responsibility rather than a charitable exception.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="reveal">
        <h2 class="font-serif text-[24px] text-navy mb-4">The Approach: Communication Built on a Foundational Belief</h2>
        <p class="text-[16px] leading-[1.8] text-text-muted mb-4">
          My role as Co-Founder and Communications Lead was to translate this philosophy into a tangible narrative strategy. Every tactic was filtered through Tama PR&rsquo;s core lenses to ensure alignment between word and mission:
        </p>
        <ul class="space-y-4 text-[15px] text-text-muted">
          <li class="flex gap-3"><span class="text-terracotta mt-1">&#9679;</span> <span><strong class="text-navy">Through the Lens of Advocacy & Ethical Storytelling:</strong> This pillar became our non-negotiable standard. We established protocols to ensure every community narrative was shared with dignity, context, and consent, transforming storytelling from extraction into a practice of partnership.</span></li>
          <li class="flex gap-3"><span class="text-terracotta mt-1">&#9679;</span> <span><strong class="text-navy">Through the Lens of Communication & PR Education:</strong> We focused on building the team&rsquo;s internal capacity, training them to become clear, confident storytellers of their own work. This turned mission clarity into external credibility and empowered the organization to own its voice.</span></li>
          <li class="flex gap-3"><span class="text-terracotta mt-1">&#9679;</span> <span><strong class="text-navy">Through the Lens of Personal Branding & Voice:</strong> We defined AECA&rsquo;s organizational voice to be as authentic and principled as its mission&mdash;a consistent voice that could build trust with donors, partners, and the communities served.</span></li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="reveal">
        <h2 class="font-serif text-[24px] text-navy mb-4">The Work: Operationalizing the Vision</h2>
        <p class="text-[16px] leading-[1.8] text-text-muted mb-4">
          Guided by the shared philosophy above, our collaboration focused on building sustainable systems, not just one-time content:
        </p>
        <ul class="space-y-3 text-[15px] text-text-muted">
          <li class="flex gap-3"><span class="text-terracotta mt-1">&#9679;</span> Crafted the core messaging framework that transforms complex social challenges into compelling, human-centered narratives for donors, partners, and the public</li>
          <li class="flex gap-3"><span class="text-terracotta mt-1">&#9679;</span> Guided ethical storytelling practices that ensure community members are active participants in their stories, protecting agency and dignity</li>
          <li class="flex gap-3"><span class="text-terracotta mt-1">&#9679;</span> Developed strategic communication plans that bridge immediate impact reporting with long-term advocacy goals, ensuring every piece of content serves the overarching vision of systemic change</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="reveal">
        <h2 class="font-serif text-[24px] text-navy mb-4">The Impact: A Credible Voice for a Transformative Vision</h2>
        <div class="space-y-4 text-[15px] text-text-muted">
          <p><strong class="text-navy">For AECA:</strong> Achieved increased visibility and credibility within critical networks by presenting a consistently clear, principled, and professional voice. The team gained the internal frameworks and confidence to communicate their impact powerfully.</p>
          <p><strong class="text-navy">For the Mission:</strong> Elevated storytelling from a marketing tool to a core practice of empowerment, ensuring narrative integrity is woven into all advocacy and engagement.</p>
          <p><strong class="text-navy">For Tama PR:</strong> This project is the living embodiment of our ethos. It demonstrates that communication, when rooted in deep philosophical alignment, becomes a powerful tool for protection, partnership, and profound advocacy.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Testimonial -->
      <div class="bg-cream rounded-xl p-8 border-l-4 border-terracotta reveal">
        <p class="font-serif text-[20px] italic text-navy leading-relaxed mb-3">
          &ldquo;Tama helped us understand that our story isn&rsquo;t something we tell&mdash;it&rsquo;s something we live.&rdquo;
        </p>
        <span class="text-[13px] text-terracotta font-medium">&mdash; Evans Odhiambo, Executive Director</span>
      </div>

      <div class="text-center pt-4 reveal">
        <h2 class="font-serif text-[24px] text-navy mb-4">If Your Organization Handles Sensitive Stories</h2>
        <p class="text-[16px] text-text-muted mb-6">You need communication that protects as much as it amplifies. Let&rsquo;s build that together.</p>
        <MagneticButton href="/contact" variant="primary">Let's Talk About Your Advocacy Work</MagneticButton>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

</BaseLayout>
